	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You're always going to run that risk, short of citing <em>only</em> scholarly journals, and even then, <a href="http://www.iflscience.com/technology/journal-accepts-paper-reading-get-me-your-fucking-mailing-list" class="postlink">you're still running the same risk</a>. Just face it, you always need to be skeptical of information regardless of where it comes from, and pinning the blame on Wikipedia isn't going to solve your problems.<br /><br />Wikipedia isn't any worse than using Google to find random webpages for information, so what's the complaint?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


